# C.O.R.E-AI
C.O.R.E. is an interactive AI-based Chatbot application developed using the C programming language. In an era where artificial intelligence is transforming human-machine interaction, this project aims to demonstrate how a rule-based system can effectively communicate, assist, and provide information to users in a terminal environment.
Introduction:
Welcome to our GOLD PROJECT. The project, titled C.O.R.E. (Created Only Remembering
Everyone), is an interactive AI-based Chatbot application developed using the C programming
language. In an era where artificial intelligence is transforming human-machine interaction, this project
aims to demonstrate how a rule-based system can effectively communicate, assist, and provide
information to users in a terminal environment.
The primary objective of C.O.R.E. is to provide a seamless user experience by combining logic-driven
responses with a personalized touch. Unlike traditional command-line programs, this chatbot features a
stylized interface using ANSI color sequences and a persistent memory system to recognize the user. It
is designed to handle various tasks, including basic calculations, identity verification, and emotional tone
simulation, making it both a functional tool and an engaging companion.
Objectives:
The primary objectives of the C.O.R.E. chatbot project are as follows:
● Interactive Communication: To develop a functional terminal-based application that can simulate
human-like conversations using conditional logic and string processing in C.
● System Integration: To implement low-level system commands and Windows API configurations
(such as SetConsoleMode) to enhance the standard command-line interface.
● Persistent Data Management: To utilize file handling techniques in C, allowing the chatbot to store
and retrieve user data (like names and preferences) even after the program is closed.
● Visual Enhancement: To create an aesthetically pleasing user interface using ANSI escape
sequences for color coding and ASCII art for branding.
● Algorithm Implementation: To apply core programming concepts such as pseudorandom
number generation (srand) and control structures to provide diverse and non-repetitive
responses.
Features:
Our application highlights fourteen main features, and there's even more variety of useful tools
and options beyond these key elements. The main fourteen features are:
1. Persistent User Memory :
• Uses C file handling (.txt) to remember the user's name and details
across different sessions.
2. Session History Logging :
• Every interaction is recorded with a timestamp in history.txt, creating a permanent log of
conversations that can be reviewed or cleared by the user.
3. Gamified Riddle Engine :
• A built-in challenge module presents random riddles with a scoring
system and a "hint" feature to keep the user engaged.
4. Integrated Mathematical Solver:
The bot processes string inputs to perform arithmetic operations like addition, subtraction,
multiplication, and division using sscanf logic.
5.Advanced ANSI TrueColor UI :
• By leveraging the Windows API, the interface displays high-end colors like Gold and Navy Blue,
moving beyond standard terminal limitations.
6.Dynamic ASCII Branding :
• Upon startup, the program displays a large-scale ASCII art logo of "C.O.R.E.", establishing a
unique visual identity for the "Gold Team" project.
7.Real-Time Temporal Awareness :
• The chatbot fetches the current system time and date, providing the user with accurate
information about the day and hour upon request.
8.Chronological Greeting Logic :
• The system analyzes the current hour to provide context-aware greetings, such as "Good
Morning" or "Good Night," tailored specifically to the user.
9.Humor & Roast Algorithms :
• The bot includes a database of jokes and "roasts" to simulate a witty personality and keep the
conversation lighthearted.
10.Randomized Fortune Telling :
• Using a random number generator, the AI predicts the user's "future" or provides a daily fortune,
adding an element of fun and unpredictability.
11.Heuristic Keyword Matching :
• Instead of simple commands, the bot scans user input for specific keywords (like "who," "thank,"
or "how") to provide relevant conversational replies.
12.Process Loading Simulation :
• To mimic human-like thinking or data processing, the bot uses a loading() function with timed
delays to create a realistic AI feel.
13.Global Scoring System :
• The program tracks a "Session Score" based on riddle accuracy and math solutions, encouraging
the user to beat their previous high score.
14.Intelligent Fallback System :
• When the input is unrecognized, the bot selects from a variety of "fallback" responses to ensure
the conversation never hits a dead end.
Tools:
We made our C.O.R.E. very carefully using strong tools and technologies. This helps make
sure that when people use it, everything works smoothly, and they can easily do what they
want on the website.
• Programming Language (C Language): The core logic, file handling, and string
processing of the chatbot are entirely developed using the C programming language.
• VS Code: This integrated development environment is used to write, debug, and manage
the C.O.R.E.c source file.
• Compiler: GCC (MinGW): The GNU Compiler Collection is utilized to transform the C
source code into an executable .txt file for Windows.
• Operating System: Windows 10/11: The project is specifically designed for the Windows
environment, utilizing Windows-specific headers like windows.h.
• Header Files: <stdio.h> , <stdlib.h>,<string.h>&<time.h>.
• File System (TXT Database): Plain text files (profile.txt and history.txt) act as a
lightweight database tool to store user data and chat logs.
Design:
Flowchart of the Design:
1. Start —> Load User Profile.
2. Input —> User types a message.
3. Process —> Search for Keywords (Riddle, Math, Story, etc.).
4. Execute —> Perform the specific function and update scores.
5. Save —> Log the message in history and save the profile.
6. Loop —> Return to Step 2 until "/exit" is typed.
